          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 neutron generator, the yield is",
                "               approximately 3.0E10 n/4Pi/s"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The T(d,n)4He reaction with a deuteron beam",
                "      (250 keV, 180 uA) produced 14 MeV neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-238",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two natural U3O8 powder samples",
                " (99.9% purity) were made into round disks of 20 mm",
                "diameter with thicknesses 1.1 mm (U-1 sample) and",
                "1.0 mm (U-2 sample). Each sample was placed between",
                "a Nb foil (20 mm diameter, 0.01 mm thickness,",
                "99.999% purity) and Zr foil (20 mm diameter,",
                "0.01 mm thickness, 99.99% purity). The sandwich",
                "sample was covered with a Cd box for preventing",
                "scattering of thermal neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Au-Si detector relative to the deuteron",
                "beam at 135 deg monitored the accompanying 4He",
                "particle to measure the neutron yield and neutron",
                "flux per 10 s, which would give a correction for",
                "neutron fluctuation."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A series of standard point sources (22Na,",
                "60Co, 133Ba,137Cs, 152Eu) of known activity were used",
                "to determine the absolute full energy peak efficiency",
                "of a lead-shielded high purity germanium detector",
                "with a relative efficiency of 68% and an energy",
                "resolution of 1.82 keV at 1.33 MeV for 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The irradiation time of the U-1 sample was",
                "60 min for the measurement of fission product nuclei",
                "with a lifetime of a few hours. To measure",
                "longer-lived fission product nuclei, the U-2 sample",
                "was irradiated for 17 h. The U-1 sample was measured",
                "at a distance of 9 cm from the detector after",
                "76.53 min of cooling. The U-1 and U-2 samples were",
                "measured after 22.08 h and 20.59 days, respectively,",
                "at a distance of 4.5 cm from the detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
